    "The prediction value of an active user u a on a target item denoted as P u a,I i, is defined using the weighted sum method as shown in the following Formula:where the item I q ∈ K i, K i denotes the set of the most similar items to the target item I i and is rated also by the active user u a, r u,I q denotes the rating of an item I q by the user u a, TotalSim(I i, I q) denotes the combined similarity value of the target item I i and I q which is calculated by Formula 9.",
    "The predicted rating values of unseen items for the user u a are stored as a vector the prediction matrix P u a [1 × n].Based on the matrix P u a [1 × n], all unseen items will be sorted in descending order according to their predicted rating values and then the top-N items will be generated as the most relevant recommendations for the given user.",
